Description:
    This document is used to describe how to integrate MoCA API on linux platform.

Directories and files:
    (1)	Library: lib/
    (2)	Binary: bin/
    (3)	Headers of libmoca2: include/
    (4)	Script of MoCA daemon: etc/mocad2Init

Installation flow:
    (1)	Install library on linux file system.
    (2)	Install binary on linux file system.
    (3)	Install MoCA daemon script on linux file system.    
    (4)	Modify the script of MoCA daemon if the network interface between host and MoCA device is not ¡§br0¡¨
        Example: If the network interface between host and MoCA device is ¡§eth0¡¨, modify the start function of script as follow:
                 mocad2 eth0 -log 0&
    (5)	Start MoCA daemon before using libmoca2.
        (Recommend to start MoCA daemon after system power on)

How to start/stop MoCA daemon?
    1.	Using script: (recommended)
        1.1 Start daemon: mocad2Init start
        1.2 Stop daemon: mocad2Init stop
    2.	Using command in command line:
        2.1 Start daemon: mocad2 br0 -log 0&
        2.2 Stop daemon: killall mocad2; rm /tmp/mocad2

How to use libmoca2?
    Please reference to include/libMoca.h

How to test libmoca2 in command line?
    Please use command ¡§testMoca2¡¨. ( ¡§testMoca2 -h¡¨ to get more information) 

System requirements:
    1. libpcap (Please get version 1.0.0 source code form http://www.tcpdump.org/)
    2. libpthread
    3. libstdc++
    4. Kernel support "Unix domain sockets"
